ce:section.ce:para:
In the present study, the CDs were prepared by a facile one-pot hydrothermal pyrolysis of CA and MEA at 180 °C for 4 h. The superiority of this synthesis method is simple product purification, which only need remove the solvent by rotary evaporation. The possible procedure of the CDs formation was proposed that a cross-linked network intermediate was firstly formed by condensation polymerization between citric acid and monoethanolamine, then the condensed polymers were carbonized to form CDs (Scheme 1
                        ). The morphology and the size of the CDs were well characterized by TEM, the morphology of the CDs was nearly spherical with some irregularity (Fig. 1
                        a), and the particle size was distributed in a wide range with an average diameter of 13.7 nm (Inset in Fig. 1a).
